<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Novandamus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I'll break the idea down to the simplest form: buildable and destroyable buildings/towns/empires that are COMPLETELY player run. ALL else is just extra tassles on that nipple ornament boys. When you have PC's working together and building a town and then other players raiding that town or allying with it or whatever you have a game that will last longer than anything coming out or that will come out. Now just add the extras. A pvp oriented skill/level or just skill system. Anything that is balanced and has some strategy to it. You know the rest cause we've seen the rest in AC/EQ/UO. Who wouldn't come back to a game day after day because you didn't know if your town was still there or was finished yet or if your clan had taken a town. That ALONE would bring people back for years. All we can do is wait eh? Or maybe one of these companies will see my genius and hire me  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif">.<P><BR>Novandamis Unifradim<BR>Novandamus@hotmail.com</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Medieval Buzz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I happen to think Atriarch is going to come really close to that type of thing if all the press releases to date can be believed. I'm holding out hope. I've already given up on Asheron's Call being a really deep, involving  game. I'm still going to buy it, but I've come realize that I need to approach it as more of a first person shooter type of experience and not expect anything more out of it as to keep my dissapointment level down. Superficial fun at best. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
